description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for full time permanent Band 5 staff nurses&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;br /&gt;Applications are invited from persons with a Nursing Degree or RNLD with relevant experience and registered with NMC to join a progressive team to provide a high quality service to people with learning disabilities. The post will require you to work in inpatient services in north Wales.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The successful applicants will support the Ward Managers to provide quality care for individuals with Learning Disabilities and associated complex health needs. As a key member of the team you should possess good interpersonal and communication skills (both written and verbal), and be able to lead and motivate others. You should also be willing to work flexibly within a team.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The postholder will be required to travel in a timely manner and the ability to speak Welsh would be desirable.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; Welsh and/or English speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing Date: 18/11/20&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Cleo Roberts&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ward Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Cleo.roberts@wales.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
